## Executive Summary

This audit examined the AutoGPT platform's governance controls, specifically focusing on authorization, Human-in-the-Loop (HITL) enforcement, escalation handling, and logging.

**Key Finding:** The HITL implementation contains a critical bypass. When `human_in_the_loop_safe_mode` is disabled, all HITL blocks auto-approve without any human review. This mirrors the simulated HITL pattern identified in earlier healthcare system audits.

**Risk Severity:** HIGH (10x on severity scale)

