Recommendations
For AutoGPT Developers
Priority	Recommendation
1	Remove or hard-enable safe mode. HITL should never be bypassable via configuration.
2	Add explicit warnings when safe mode is disabled.
3	Require multi-factor approval for high-severity actions.
4	Log all HITL bypass events to an immutable audit trail.
For Organizations Deploying AutoGPT
Priority	Recommendation
1	Verify human_in_the_loop_safe_mode is enabled in production.
2	Test HITL blocks with a simple workflow before deployment.
3	Monitor logs for "skipping review" messages.
4	Treat HITL as a critical control, not a convenience feature.
